That's for exhaust gas recirculation.  It wouldn't affect your brake 
operation.

> things that should be replaced?  My fuel lines are all the braided cloth
> type, should I replace these?  I am planning a complete electrical rebuild

If you bend them and they crack, then replace them.  Heck, if you can't 
guarantee that they are in fact good, I would replace every single fuel 
line on the bus.  There is a fuel diagram somewhere on richard's website:

www.ratwell.com

Fuel lines are good insurance so you don't end up with a burnt bus!

